{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e40d79e3-5ef6-4f92-9c04-c31f87ce60ee","content":"For a .NET Web API project, use the **`webapi`** template:\n\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi -n MyApi\n```\n\n### Authentication Options (`--auth`)\n\n| Option | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `None` | No authentication (default) |\n| `IndividualB2C` | Azure AD B2C individual accounts |\n| `SingleOrg` | Single-tenant Azure AD (org accounts) |\n| `MultiOrg` | Multi-tenant Azure AD |\n| `Windows` | Windows/Negotiate authentication |\n\n### Examples\n\n```bash\n# Azure AD single-org auth\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg --domain yourdomain.com --tenant-id <id> --client-id <id>\n\n# Azure AD B2C\ndotnet new webapi --auth IndividualB2C\n\n# Minimal API style (default in .NET 6+)\ndotnet new webapi --use-minimal-apis\n```\n\nYou can also add JWT Bearer auth manually via `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.JwtBearer` if you need custom identity provider support (e.g., Auth0, Keycloak).\n\nWant me to scaffold a project with a specific auth configuration?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"06409162-03cb-409d-ab85-dd840e3150cd","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about web API project templates and authentication options. This is a general knowledge question about .NET (likely, given the repository context with dotnet plugins). I can answer this from my knowledge without needing to search the codebase.","outputTokens":349,"requestId":"9C05:3BE8A6:1CCF6F6:2043AAC:6A07BF5B"},"id":"e0c0e1ac-7849-4412-9c2f-f9ab8844c1e0","timestamp":"2026-05-16T00:50:44.198Z","parentId":"4a8bb7e7-36d1-409e-92d8-e81a4c6097ab"}
